observations.recommendation:
Municipal Engineer issue Certificates of Completion for the completed projects to be used as basis by the Municipal Accountant in the reclassification of these items to their proper PPE account.

Municipal Accountant take up the corresponding depreciation expenses of these projects from the time these were completed until December 31, 2023; 

Municipal Engineer submit request for relief from accountability for lost construction materials supported with complete documentation to the audit team for evaluation. In the meantime, the Municipal Accountant make an appropriate disclosure of these balances in the notes to financial statements; 

Municipal Accountant trace the composition of the amounts booked as beginning balances as of January 2016 and verify the actual physical status of the identified projects in order to prepare the appropriate entries to reclassify all completed projects to its appropriate property, plant and equipment accounts in accordance with pertinent rules and regulations; and 

Municipal Accountant reconcile the amounts recorded in the ledger with the amounts incurred to date recorded by the Engineering department so as to present fairly the financial statements of the Municipality as at a given period.

Require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a duly certified list showing the names of the taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year which data should come from the Real Property Tax Account Register (RPTAR) or Taxpayer’s Index Card maintained at the Municipal Treasurer’s Office;

Furnish the Municipal Accountant a copy of the certified list to serve as basis in recording the Real Property Tax Receivable and Special Education Tax Receivable accounts in the books; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to record the receivables based on the list furnished by the Municipal Treasurer in order to recognize in the books an accurate and verifiable data pursuant to Sections 19 and 20 of the NGAS Manual, Volume 1.

Municipal Accountant to inform/communicate with the depository banks on the errors and unreconciled deposits in transit, and thereafter, effect the necessary adjustments;

Municipal Accountant to take notice of the existence of any stale checks at the end of the month (those outstanding for over 6 months from date of check) and communicate such information to the Treasurer’s Office so that proper action can be initiated and pertinent adjustments be effected in the books; 

Municipal Treasurer to forward immediately the paid vouchers and supporting documents pertaining to the unrecorded disbursements in item (d) for recording to avoid overstatement of the cash account; and

Municipal Treasurer to immediately notify the Accounting Office upon receipt of a debit memo from the bank so that appropriate adjustment be effected in the books.

The Management to immediately remit to the Bureau of the Treasury the unutilized PDAF and CDF pursuant to the Supreme Court Decision dated November 13, 2013 to prevent misuse or misappropriation thereof;

Coordinate with the source agencies and request for authority to transfer the unexpended balances to the General Fund of the Municipality. Otherwise, return the unexpended balance to the source agencies, whichever is appropriate and submit to the Audit Team the corresponding liquidation report and other pertinent documents for post-audit; and

Direct the Municipal Accountant to review the SLs with negative balances and trace the cause/s thereof and thereafter, make the necessary adjusting entry to reflect the correct balances.  Also, indicate the appropriate descriptions in the subsidiary ledger such as the project/program names, source agencies and the date of the fund transfer to facilitate monitoring.

